.TH STASH 1 "2026-03-19" "stash v0.4.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
stash \- personal knowledge vault
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B stash
.RI [ command ]
.RI [ flags ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B stash
captures, organizes, and searches URLs, text snippets, files, directories,
images, and email messages. All content is stored locally with full-text
search powered by SQLite FTS5.
.PP
Running
.B stash
with no arguments launches the interactive TUI.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.B add \fI<url|file|dir|->\fR
Stash a URL, file, directory, or stdin snippet. URLs are fetched and
content is extracted automatically. Files are stored in a content-addressable
store and text is extracted when possible. Directories are automatically
archived as tar.gz before storing. Use \fB-\fR to read from stdin.
.TP
.B list
List stashed items, optionally filtered by type, tag, collection, or
date range.
.TP
.B search \fI<query>\fR
Full-text search across all stashed content.
.TP
.B show \fI<id>\fR
Show details of a stashed item. Accepts prefix IDs (minimum 6 characters).
Archive items (tar.gz, zip) display a tree listing of their contents.
.TP
.B edit \fI<id>\fR
Edit a stashed item's title, notes, tags, or extracted text.
.TP
.B delete \fI<id>\fR
Delete a stashed item. Prompts for confirmation unless \fB-y\fR is given.
.TP
.B open \fI<id>\fR
Open a stashed item in its default application.
.TP
.B link \fI<id1> <id2>\fR
Create a link between two items. Use \fB-l\fR to add a label
and \fB--directed\fR for a one-way link.
.TP
.B unlink \fI<id1> <id2>\fR
Remove a link between two items.
.TP
.B tag list
List all tags.
.TP
.B tag rename \fI<old> <new>\fR
Rename a tag across all items.
.TP
.B collection list
List all collections.
.TP
.B collection create \fI<name>\fR
Create a new collection. Use \fB-d\fR to set a description.
.TP
.B collection show \fI<name>\fR
Show items in a collection.
.TP
.B collection delete \fI<name>\fR
Delete a collection (items are retained).
.TP
.B ui\fR, \fBtui
Launch the interactive terminal UI.
.TP
.B man
Display this manual page.
.SH OPTIONS
.SS Global Flags
.TP
.B \-\-json
Output as JSON.
.TP
.B \-\-db \fI<path>\fR
Custom database path.
.TP
.B \-\-help
Show help.
.TP
.B \-\-version
Show version.
.SS Add Flags
.TP
.B \-t\fR, \fB\-\-title \fI<title>\fR
Set a custom title (auto-detected if omitted).
.TP
.B \-T\fR, \fB\-\-tag \fI<tag>\fR
Add tags (repeatable).
.TP
.B \-n\fR, \fB\-\-note \fI<note>\fR
Attach a note.
.TP
.B \-c\fR, \fB\-\-collection \fI<name>\fR
Add to a collection.
.TP
.B \-\-type \fI<type>\fR
Force item type: link, snippet, file, image, email.
.TP
.B \-d\fR, \fB\-\-delete
Delete the source file or directory after a successful stash.
Only applies to file and directory sources, not URLs or stdin.
.SS Link Flags
.TP
.B \-l\fR, \fB\-\-label \fI<label>\fR
Add a label to the link.
.TP
.B \-\-directed
Create a directed link (from id1 to id2).
.SS Edit Flags
.TP
.B \-t\fR, \fB\-\-title \fI<title>\fR
Set a new title.
.TP
.B \-n\fR, \fB\-\-note \fI<note>\fR
Set a new note.
.TP
.B \-e\fR, \fB\-\-extracted\-text \fI<text>\fR
Set the extracted text content.
.TP
.B \-\-add\-tag \fI<tag>\fR
Add a tag (repeatable).
.TP
.B \-\-remove\-tag \fI<tag>\fR
Remove a tag (repeatable).
.TP
.B \-c\fR, \fB\-\-collection \fI<name>\fR
Add to a collection.
.SS Filter Flags (list, search)
.TP
.B \-\-type \fI<type>\fR
Filter by item type.
.TP
.B \-\-tag \fI<tag>\fR
Filter by tag.
.TP
.B \-\-collection \fI<name>\fR
Filter by collection.
.TP
.B \-\-after \fI<date>\fR
Show items created after this date.
.TP
.B \-\-before \fI<date>\fR
Show items created before this date.
.TP
.B \-l\fR, \fB\-\-limit \fI<n>\fR
Maximum number of results (default 50).
.SH INTERACTIVE KEYS
The TUI supports the following keys:
.TP
.B /
Open search. Supports \fBtag:\fIname\fR filter syntax.
.TP
.B 1\-5
Toggle type filter (1=urls, 2=snippets, 3=files, 4=images, 5=emails).
.TP
.B j/k \fRor\fB Up/Down
Navigate items.
.TP
.B Enter
View item detail.
.TP
.B o
Open item in default application. Archives are extracted to a temp directory.
.TP
.B d
Delete item (prompts for y/n confirmation).
.TP
.B l
Link current item to another (search and select).
.TP
.B u
Unlink a linked item (select from list).
.TP
.B r
Refresh item list.
.TP
.B q
Quit (list view) or go back (detail view).
.TP
.B Ctrl+C
Force quit.
.TP
.B Ctrl+L
Clear search and filters.
.SH ITEM TYPES
.TP
.B link
Bookmarked URLs. Content is fetched and extracted via readability.
.TP
.B snippet
Text captured from stdin.
.TP
.B file
Local files stored in the content-addressable file store.
.TP
.B image
Image files with metadata extraction.
.TP
.B email
RFC 2822 email messages (.eml files) with header and body extraction.
.SH CONFIGURATION
Configuration is read from \fI~/.config/stash/config.toml\fR:
.PP
.nf
data_dir     = "~/.stash"
db_path      = "~/.stash/stash.db"
files_dir    = "~/.stash/files"
image_viewer = ""  # custom image viewer command
.fi
.PP
Precedence: CLI flags > \fBSTASH_DIR\fR env var > config file > defaults.
.SH FILES
.TP
.I ~/.config/stash/config.toml
Configuration file.
.TP
.I ~/.stash/stash.db
SQLite database with FTS5 full-text search.
.TP
.I ~/.stash/files/
Content-addressable file store (SHA-256).
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B STASH_DIR
Override the data directory (default: \fI~/.stash\fR).
.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Success.
.TP
.B 1
Error.
